data.text: Went in for a Sweet Tea and i would have to say that it was terrible it wasn't sweet at all and the restaurant was dirty.

data.title: As good as any!
data.text: We live near this McDonald's so frequent it often.  Have no complaints.  Food is always hot, restaurant is always clean.  Spent a lot of time here with grandkids in Playland.

data.title: Not what you expect to get
data.text:
I don't normally write a review about a McDonalds - most of us have been to this chain enough that we know what to expect right?

Not exactly the case on my recent visit here.

Got there shortly after the lunch menu started being served and was surprised how dirty the beverage station was.  Spilled ketchup, wrappers, etc.  Not really surprised by this part - but what stood out to me was when I started getting some ketchup - it was not good.  It actually came out in my cup a two-toned color and very, very watery - not sure if watered down to try and save money - but I was not impressed.

Got my big mac, ketchup even tasted off - like watered down ketchup - don't recall this type of experience at other McD - but perhaps you have.  Didn't even finish my sandwich - fries were not very hot and slightly overcooked.  Saw another woman eating and the middle of her burger was pretty pink/undercooked.

So, I guess not all McDonalds are alike - normally yes, but not this one. 

Probably will not be back.

data.title: Bad food
data.text: My husband and I went there for a quick meal. I ordered Big Mac. I ate almost half of it and then started to gag. Within 30 minutes I was soooo sick, I thought I was goint to vomit I will NEVER eat at McDonalds again!
